   <text>
      <body>
         <pb n="101"/>
         <milestone n="101" unit="page"/>
         <lb/>
         <lb/>
         <head>
            <emph>LINES <lb/>
               <lb/>Written when sailing in a Boat <lb/>
               <lb/>At
                            EVENING.</emph>
         </head>
         <lg n="1" type="stanza">
            <l n="1">How rich the wave, in front, imprest </l>
            <l n="2">With evening twilight’s summer hues, </l>
            <l n="3">While, facing thus the crimson west, </l>
            <l n="4">The boat her silent course pursues ! </l>
            <l n="5">And see how dark the backward stream ! </l>
            <l n="6">A little moment past, so smiling ! </l>
            <l n="7">And still, perhaps, with faithless gleam, </l>
            <l n="8">Some other loiterer beguiling. </l>
         </lg>
         <pb/>
         <milestone n="102" unit="page"/>
         <lb/>
         <lb/>
         <lg n="2" type="stanza">
            <l n="9">Such views the youthful bard allure,</l>
            <l n="10">But, heedless of the following gloom, </l>
            <l n="11">He deems their colours shall endure </l>
            <l n="12">’Till peace go with him to the tomb.</l>
            <l n="13">—And let him nurse his fond deceit, </l>
            <l n="14">And what if he must die in sorrow !</l>
            <l n="15">Who would not cherish dreams so sweet,</l>
            <l n="16">Though grief and pain may come to-morrow ?</l>
         </lg>
      </body>
